parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to a lack of proper restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle comes loose or detaches from the frame
the buckle fails to latch properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold can cause carbon monoxide to leak into the engine compartment or passenger compartment, posing a significant risk to the health and safety of occupants.
symptoms: Exhaust manifold studs break or become loose
carbon monoxide leaks into the engine compartment or passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Tire tread comes off while driving
tire tread separation occurs under wet conditions
and vehicle becomes difficult to control.
